               <p>THOMAS HORSLEY. I am a <rs id="t18280221-218-viclabel1160" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-218-victim1275 t18280221-218-viclabel1160"></join>. My son Matthew and his sister went to school on the 8th of February, a little after twelve o'clock; his sister came home without him - a man brought him home between one and two o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-218-person1277">
                  GEORGE 
                  HULL
               <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1277" type="surname" value="HULL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1277" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter. On the 8th of February, about noon, I was coming out of my house, and heard a man had taken a pair of shoes from a child; I went in pursuit, and came up to the prisoner - I asked if he had not taken a pair of shoes from a child; he said No, that he had just come from Bow, and had seen none; I said he could not come from Bow that way. I took his hat off, and there found the shoes - I gave him to an officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-218-person1278">
                  JOHN 
                  MARSH CATT
               <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1278" type="surname" value="MARSH CATT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1278" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-218-person1278" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I came up, and took the prisoner; in about five minutes the mother brought the child into the public-house; there were a dozen people there - I asked the child to point out the person who took the shoes; he pointed to the prisoner immediately, and said,</p>
               <p>"That is the man, but he did not give me the penny"- the prisoner said he found the shoes on a bank.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that he had found the shoes in a field, and put them into his hat; and had not seen the child.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280221-218-verdict1161" type="verdictDescription">
